1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:12,720
Whoa!

3
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,240
What's going on?

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,400
Hey...

5
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,240
Look.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,240
You were such a cute kid.

7
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:30,960
Are these...your parents?

8
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:37,960
Mm.

9
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:43,760
Why haven't you told me about your family?

10
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,640
It was a long time ago.

11
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,360
Just help me pack.

12
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:04,760
Though...

13
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,400
You looked so happy as a child, didn't you?

14
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,840
Your smile,

15
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:13,760
your parents' smiles,

16
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,560
and the birthday cake.

17
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:21,560
The happiness in their eyes truly doesn't lie.

18
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,680
Ugh!

19
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,640
What kind of girlfriend am I?

20
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,280
What now?

21
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,000
I don't even know your birthday.

22
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:44,040
Ugh! It's not a big deal at all.

23
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,960
So when were you born?

24
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,840
I'm not telling you.

25
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:47,720
What?

26
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,280
It's just a birthday, so why aren't you telling me?

27
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,240
It's just another day.

28
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:57,440
Plus, I haven't had a birthday party for so many years now.

29
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,840
It's nothing important.

30
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,080
Now, please help me pack.

31
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,480
You...

32
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,840
On this slideshow,

33
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:15,680
you'll see the names of the shareholders

34
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,640
the number of shares from last year,

35
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:25,720
and the adjustment of the shareholding ratios.

36
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,760
May I ask you a question?

37
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,640
The anonymous shareholder,

38
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,200
who are they?

39
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,840
Right now, they are the ones with the most shares at hand.

40
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:47,280
Their decisions will affect W Empire's management direction.

41
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,440
That's why I'm curious.

42
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,040
No need to worry.

43
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,320
This shareholder

44
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,160
won't interfere with management.

45
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,800
The authority in decision-making

46
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,200
is still mine.

47
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,880
Understood.

48
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,960
If the decisions are yours,

49
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,040
I'm relieved.

50
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,320
From now on,

51
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:20,440
Ms. Arisa is officially part of our organization.

52
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:23,200
W Empire and Alist

53
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,080
are now family.

54
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,920
As the CEO,

55
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,640
I would like everyone to welcome her with a round of applause.

56
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,280
Why don't you ask my boss yourself, Ms. Lalin?

57
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,040
It's just a small question.

58
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,640
You don't have to ask me.

59
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,560
Well, that boss of yours keeps dancing around it.

60
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,400
When is she ever going to tell me?

61
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,200
Ooh...

62
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,120
If she refuses to tell you,

63
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,360
I wouldn't dare answer.

64
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,640
So...

65
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,280
why do you need her birthday, Ms. Lalin?

66
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,960
Is it for fortune-telling?

67
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,600
She's not superstitious, though.

68
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,240
It's not!

69
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:26,280
I just wanna plan a surprise for her.

70
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:31,240
I happened to see the photos of her younger self blowing candles with her parents.

71
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:34,120
She seemed so happy.

72
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:38,120
I want her to be able to experience it again. It's gonna be really nice.

73
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:40,440
Excuse me.

74
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:44,320
I wouldn't dare tell you since she's gonna tell me off.

75
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,640
Besides...

76
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,320
she doesn't like surprises.

77
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,360
Is she gatekeeping her birthdate as some kind of lucky number?

78
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:56,360
Please, Ms. Aiy. Please?

79
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,480
I just wanna be a good partner.

80
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,200
Don't you feel bad that she'd have to spend her birthday alone?

81
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,240
Please?

82
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,640
Please help me out.

83
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,800
I just wanna be a good partner.

84
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:12,360
Would you please help me?

85
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,480
Please help me!

86
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,520
Even though I'm single,

87
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,160
I'd like to cherish these kinds of moments for once.

88
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:27,400
And even though she's gonna tell me off,

89
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,880
I'll help you, Ms. Lalin.

90
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,240
You will?

91
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,480
Thank you, Ms. Aiy. Thank you.

92
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,680
Here.

93
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:39,520
Cheers.

94
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,040
Good luck.

95
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,200
Good luck to me, too.

96
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:56,240
I've brought you your favorite white flowers.

97
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,840
My birthday arrives in two weeks.

98
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,080
I wish you and Dad were here to wish me a happy birthday.

99
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,880
No matter how tired I may be,

100
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:16,040
I will bring back our family's dignity.

101
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:21,280
I don't know if another life exists,

102
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,600
but if it does...

103
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,000
I'd like to meet you guys again.

104
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,840
But if not,

105
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,760
please appear in my dreams once in a while.

106
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,280
I promise

107
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:39,520
that I will make sure to put those who tore us apart

108
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:42,480
in the deepest agony,

109
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,400
just the same way they did to me.

110
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,240
What is it?

111
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,640
It's the person we're looking for.

112
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,960
The anonymous shareholder.

113
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,640
Her name is Ruwajee,

114
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,280
the older sister of Thana, Weiling's husband,

115
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,160
who was also Lalin's father.

116
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:20,840
She received the shares from a transfer her brother made in his will,

117
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,640
and ever since he passed away,

118
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:27,200
she distanced herself from W Empire

119
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,080
to live a life on her own

120
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,160
with no husband or family,

121
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:34,400
and barely any contact with Weiling.

122
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,600
Partly because

123
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,960
she has a gambling problem.

124
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,280
Miss,

125
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:05,000
care for some cookies?

126
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,280
Here you go.

127
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,280
Wow, that looks appetizing.

128
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,600
I was just craving desserts.

129
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,280
Please get up.

130
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,840
Huh?

131
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,160
Please.

132
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,760
Now, please sit.

133
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,960
What's going on?

134
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,520
It just happened...

135
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,280
that we offer a delivery service

136
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,880
straight to your lips.

137
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,400
Since when did you become such a teaser?

138
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:55,480
Are you interested in our service?

139
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,400
So where is it?

140
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,480
Is it good?

141
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,200
It is.

142
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,080
Dear customer,

143
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,320
you got it on your lips.

144
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,840
All clean.

145
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,760
Jeez, you...

146
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:17,320
If I can have something as delicious as this every day,

147
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:20,120
I don't think I'd ever have to go out.

148
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,160
You know,

149
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,800
the pros of us working together are that

150
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:29,160
you can charge your battery with me whenever you want

151
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,760
and however much you want.

152
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:36,440
Then I'll charge it to the brim.

153
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,600
Ow! Dear...

154
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,000
Refreshing!

155
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,640
Enough, enough, enough, enough, enough.

156
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,680
- You... - That's full battery for me.

157
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,200
What do you think?

158
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:54,280
How do you find my service?

159
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,480
I like it.

160
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,520
This is tasty.

161
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,840
- Right, dear. - Hm?

162
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:13,480
Another one of the shareholders

163
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,240
who remains anonymous,

164
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:18,200
who...are they?

165
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,840
Mm,

166
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,880
it's Auntie Ruwajee.

167
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,640
And who is she?

168
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,800
She is my father's older sister,

169
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,280
but she and Mom never really got along,

170
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:33,400
so she gave Mom the company's management authority.

171
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:38,360
Speaking of which, I kinda miss her.

172
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:40,400
It's been a while since I've seen her.

173
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,520
How about this?

174
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:47,880
I'll take you to see her to fix that. How does that sound?

175
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,240
Nice!

176
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:52,240
I think that

177
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,200
Auntie's gonna like you,

178
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:57,960
just like how everyone does.

179
00:13:36,057 --> 00:13:37,923
Ooh! That's gratifying.

180
00:13:37,957 --> 00:13:40,990
Let me hug and kiss you until I'm satisfied.

181
00:13:41,223 --> 00:13:43,090
It's been years.

182
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:45,990
You've grown into such a beautiful woman.

183
00:13:46,523 --> 00:13:48,623
I miss you, too, Auntie.

184
00:13:49,757 --> 00:13:52,023
I see that you still enjoy flower arranging.

185
00:13:52,823 --> 00:13:55,490
t's what I do to cure my loneliness.

186
00:13:55,590 --> 00:13:59,290
I'm all by myself, not with a partner like you are.

187
00:14:01,857 --> 00:14:04,190
So, you two,

188
00:14:04,257 --> 00:14:08,123
have you been together for long? Fill me in.

189
00:14:08,623 --> 00:14:10,223
It's been some time, Auntie.

190
00:14:10,523 --> 00:14:13,023
It was after Mom took me in.

191
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:20,223
I heard that you were also in real estate?

192
00:14:21,123 --> 00:14:22,123
That's correct.

193
00:14:24,623 --> 00:14:28,823
Lalin said in a phone call that Weiling isn't particularly fond of you.

194
00:14:30,090 --> 00:14:31,490
Right.

195
00:14:32,123 --> 00:14:33,890
I guess I'll have to try more

196
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:35,890
and approach her with sincerity

197
00:14:36,357 --> 00:14:40,557
to prove that I truly love her daughter.

198
00:14:43,957 --> 00:14:46,057
She wants genuineness, huh?

199
00:14:46,123 --> 00:14:49,790
Was she ever genuine toward my little brother?

200
00:14:52,190 --> 00:14:53,890
What do you mean, Auntie?

201
00:14:55,223 --> 00:14:58,090
Ugh, pay it no mind. It's all in the past.

202
00:14:58,223 --> 00:15:00,190
I don't want anything to do with her.

203
00:15:02,490 --> 00:15:04,623
She's done something in the past,

204
00:15:04,790 --> 00:15:06,623
and now, her daughter's paying for it.

205
00:15:06,657 --> 00:15:08,023
She's anxious about everything

206
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:11,057
when she should be giving you freedom.

207
00:15:14,257 --> 00:15:16,123
Don't give in to her, Arisa.

208
00:15:16,690 --> 00:15:18,557
You're the only hope

209
00:15:18,623 --> 00:15:20,590
for my niece's happiness

210
00:15:20,857 --> 00:15:23,123
and freedom from her mother.

211
00:15:27,923 --> 00:15:29,423
I can tell

212
00:15:30,057 --> 00:15:32,357
who Lalin gets her assertiveness from.

213
00:15:37,123 --> 00:15:39,123
Stay for a meal with me.

214
00:15:39,423 --> 00:15:40,423
Sure.

215
00:15:48,623 --> 00:15:50,590
Auntie seems to like you.

216
00:15:51,723 --> 00:15:53,323
Approaching the elders

217
00:15:54,023 --> 00:15:55,523
is my strong suit.

218
00:15:56,623 --> 00:15:58,523
Except for my mom.

219
00:15:59,723 --> 00:16:01,057
Dear...

220
00:16:04,057 --> 00:16:06,557
Here you go. I'm just kidding.

221
00:16:10,523 --> 00:16:11,723
Here's to you.

222
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:13,057
Thank you.

223
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,123
My judgment was right.

224
00:16:23,923 --> 00:16:26,123
I knew this woman couldn't be trusted.

225
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:32,723
But what does she need?

226
00:16:34,590 --> 00:16:36,957
How should we get this sorted, ma'am?

227
00:16:37,723 --> 00:16:39,957
Should we inform Ms. Lalin?

228
00:16:40,690 --> 00:16:41,690
Not yet.

229
00:16:43,223 --> 00:16:44,890
Lalin is absolutely obsessed with her.

230
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:46,923
She wouldn't believe us if we told her.

231
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:50,590
We need to figure out what her plan is.

232
00:16:50,657 --> 00:16:52,190
Don't let that woman find out.

233
00:16:55,823 --> 00:16:57,757
I would never let her have the last laugh.

234
00:17:08,557 --> 00:17:11,423
That's it. I fold.

235
00:17:12,023 --> 00:17:13,023
Oh?

236
00:17:16,723 --> 00:17:17,757
What about you?

237
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:21,923
I'm going all in.

238
00:17:31,657 --> 00:17:33,623
Then, I fold.

239
00:17:37,457 --> 00:17:39,590
Let me see your cards.

240
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:58,357
Goodness, I just got tricked by this girl!

241
00:17:58,890 --> 00:18:00,223
I didn't trick you.

242
00:18:00,557 --> 00:18:02,390
I just got a read on you.

243
00:18:03,790 --> 00:18:05,723
Sometimes when you play cards,

244
00:18:06,223 --> 00:18:08,657
you need to know your rivals

245
00:18:08,857 --> 00:18:10,790
and what direction they might take

246
00:18:11,223 --> 00:18:13,123
so that you can turn the tables in time.

247
00:18:13,857 --> 00:18:16,257
I'm starting to like you!

248
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:18,857
Look, seeing as how your girlfriend's this good at cards

249
00:18:18,857 --> 00:18:21,490
you need to come visit often.

250
00:18:22,157 --> 00:18:24,623
Of course, I'll bring her to visit often.

251
00:18:25,723 --> 00:18:27,390
But let's do it just for fun, alright?

252
00:18:27,823 --> 00:18:29,290
No gambling.

253
00:18:29,557 --> 00:18:30,323
Oh!

254
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:36,357
This is all for fun. It's nothing serious.

255
00:18:36,523 --> 00:18:38,857
It's an old lady's hobby.

256
00:18:39,023 --> 00:18:40,623
Let's hope that was true.

257
00:18:41,357 --> 00:18:43,323
Then, please excuse me while I use the restroom.

258
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:48,557
Hurry back.

259
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:58,623
Lalin doesn't really like it when I gamble.

260
00:18:58,990 --> 00:19:00,657
She knows I'm generous

261
00:19:00,723 --> 00:19:01,923
and not one to back down.

262
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:05,257
I could go all in just to win.

263
00:19:05,823 --> 00:19:09,257
Truthfully, it's not all that bad.

264
00:19:09,423 --> 00:19:11,990
I know my own limits.

265
00:19:12,223 --> 00:19:13,857
But I do understand that.

266
00:19:15,357 --> 00:19:17,357
Sometimes, betting

267
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:20,857
makes the games much more interesting.

268
00:19:21,890 --> 00:19:25,490
There, you get me.

269
00:19:28,923 --> 00:19:30,357
Though,

270
00:19:31,457 --> 00:19:33,290
I know Lalin is just worried about me.

271
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:36,690
She's concerned that I would fall apart because of this.

272
00:19:38,923 --> 00:19:41,190
She's such a gentle soul.

273
00:19:42,157 --> 00:19:45,057
She never means anyone harm.

274
00:19:47,123 --> 00:19:50,157
She deserves to be loved by a nice person.

275
00:19:58,490 --> 00:20:01,757
You can be that person, right, Arisa?

276
00:20:13,123 --> 00:20:14,390
Please don't worry.

277
00:20:15,957 --> 00:20:17,523
Meeting Lalin

278
00:20:17,957 --> 00:20:20,923
is the best thing that's ever happened to me.

279
00:20:24,857 --> 00:20:27,490
Don't worry about Weiling.

280
00:20:28,257 --> 00:20:30,023
Just tell me if something happens.

281
00:20:31,090 --> 00:20:32,890
For my niece's happiness,

282
00:20:33,923 --> 00:20:35,857
I will handle it for you.

283
00:20:43,823 --> 00:20:44,823
Cheers.

284
00:20:45,623 --> 00:20:47,090
Thank you.

285
00:20:49,923 --> 00:20:52,523
How do you feel? Has that longing gone away?

286
00:20:52,723 --> 00:20:55,057
It is, but I do wanna see her again.

287
00:20:55,523 --> 00:20:57,423
She seems to like you.

288
00:20:57,990 --> 00:20:59,290
I'll take you to visit her again.

289
00:20:59,890 --> 00:21:00,957
Where have you been?

290
00:21:02,623 --> 00:21:03,923
You're home late.

291
00:21:05,357 --> 00:21:07,957
I took Arisa to see Auntie Ruwajee.

292
00:21:10,023 --> 00:21:11,157
Ruwajee?

293
00:21:12,223 --> 00:21:12,990
What for?

294
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:16,723
Well, I miss her,

295
00:21:16,923 --> 00:21:18,690
so Arisa took me to visit her.

296
00:21:18,890 --> 00:21:20,823
I also wanted to introduce them to each other.

297
00:21:21,523 --> 00:21:22,590
How is this any of your business?

298
00:21:22,757 --> 00:21:23,657
Mom!

299
00:21:24,390 --> 00:21:26,490
Be nice to her.

300
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:29,890
It's just a visit. I don't see what's strange about it.

301
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:31,723
It's fine, dear.

302
00:21:34,157 --> 00:21:38,057
I just took her to visit her beloved relatives whom she respects, that's all.

303
00:21:41,157 --> 00:21:42,790
It's nice to visit senior relatives,

304
00:21:43,190 --> 00:21:44,923
but I hope that's all there is to it.

305
00:21:58,357 --> 00:22:00,023
- Dear. - Hm?

306
00:22:00,823 --> 00:22:02,257
About Auntie Ruwajee,

307
00:22:03,723 --> 00:22:06,223
hasn't she been married?

308
00:22:08,057 --> 00:22:09,123
No.

309
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:11,657
My dad used to tell me

310
00:22:12,657 --> 00:22:14,557
that she was in a relationship,

311
00:22:14,823 --> 00:22:16,423
and they met in Las Vegas.

312
00:22:17,357 --> 00:22:19,557
I suppose you can guess what kind of person they were.

313
00:22:20,857 --> 00:22:22,723
The family didn't accept it,

314
00:22:22,823 --> 00:22:27,157
and after that, I've never seen her with anyone again.

315
00:22:30,923 --> 00:22:33,423
She's been alone half her life.

316
00:22:33,923 --> 00:22:35,457
That must have been so lonely.

317
00:22:38,323 --> 00:22:39,657
It sure is.

318
00:22:39,890 --> 00:22:41,323
With how she lives alone,

319
00:22:41,557 --> 00:22:43,057
it must be really hard to do things.

320
00:22:43,823 --> 00:22:47,757
I don't even wanna imagine if I could make it on my own.

321
00:22:48,823 --> 00:22:50,323
Why do you even have to imagine that?

322
00:22:50,890 --> 00:22:52,457
You already have me!

323
00:22:52,523 --> 00:22:54,257
What's there to imagine?

324
00:22:55,823 --> 00:22:59,223
Then, promise me that we'll grow old together

325
00:22:59,823 --> 00:23:01,923
to apply my skincare like this every day.

326
00:23:05,823 --> 00:23:07,123
I promise.

327
00:23:08,090 --> 00:23:09,857
I'm not even done applying your skincare.

328
00:23:10,157 --> 00:23:11,657
Let me do it for you.

329
00:23:47,011 --> 00:23:48,444
- Hello, ma'am. - Oh?

330
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:50,777
Lalin is not with you?

331
00:23:50,911 --> 00:23:52,011
No.

332
00:23:52,311 --> 00:23:54,211
She has a meeting to attend,

333
00:23:54,277 --> 00:23:55,911
but I'm available today.

334
00:23:56,077 --> 00:23:59,844
I recall a game you used to like, and wanted to play it with you.

335
00:24:02,244 --> 00:24:03,611
What do you mean?

336
00:24:03,877 --> 00:24:05,611
It's a game of chance.

337
00:24:06,211 --> 00:24:08,244
But this is not something Lalin is good at.

338
00:24:08,311 --> 00:24:10,011
I think I'd better have you join me.

339
00:24:12,211 --> 00:24:13,744
Will it be okay?

340
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:17,577
- If Lalin finds this out... - Don't worry about it.

341
00:24:18,111 --> 00:24:21,577
This will be kept between...two of us.

342
00:24:30,111 --> 00:24:31,344
This...

343
00:24:31,477 --> 00:24:33,077
is my lucky spot.

344
00:24:33,111 --> 00:24:35,077
I used to come here pretty often.

345
00:24:35,577 --> 00:24:36,644
But now...

346
00:24:37,177 --> 00:24:39,877
I don't have much money to keep it up.

347
00:24:41,477 --> 00:24:42,544
Shall we try?

348
00:24:43,311 --> 00:24:44,311
Go ahead.

349
00:24:45,477 --> 00:24:47,277
Please place your bets.

350
00:24:58,977 --> 00:25:00,177
Time's up.

351
00:25:05,844 --> 00:25:07,344
Banker wins.

352
00:25:08,544 --> 00:25:09,544
See?

353
00:25:09,577 --> 00:25:12,311
I told you it's my lucky spot!

354
00:25:12,377 --> 00:25:13,777
I believed you.

355
00:25:14,977 --> 00:25:16,177
Player.

356
00:25:20,477 --> 00:25:21,477
Oh!

357
00:25:21,511 --> 00:25:23,144
Wow!

358
00:25:29,477 --> 00:25:31,444
- Oh! -Whoa!

359
00:25:34,277 --> 00:25:35,277
Cheers!

360
00:25:35,644 --> 00:25:36,644
Let's do it.

361
00:25:38,244 --> 00:25:39,944
- You're thrilled. - Yes, I am.

362
00:25:40,144 --> 00:25:41,844
Banker.

363
00:25:45,444 --> 00:25:46,944
It's okay, kid.

364
00:25:46,977 --> 00:25:48,911
Learn from it.

365
00:25:49,711 --> 00:25:51,544
- One more time. - Let's do it one more time.

366
00:25:57,211 --> 00:25:58,911
Wow!

367
00:25:59,077 --> 00:26:00,111
See?

368
00:26:04,544 --> 00:26:05,544
Place your bets.

369
00:26:05,611 --> 00:26:08,177
I'll bet a large amount this round.

370
00:26:16,744 --> 00:26:17,911
No more bets.

371
00:26:24,077 --> 00:26:25,277
Player wins.

372
00:26:28,344 --> 00:26:29,344
It's totally fine.

373
00:26:31,077 --> 00:26:32,111
My luck will come in the next round.

374
00:26:56,477 --> 00:26:57,677
Damn it!

375
00:27:01,611 --> 00:27:04,111
Wait...I...

376
00:27:09,544 --> 00:27:10,544
Here you go.

377
00:27:14,044 --> 00:27:16,744
I'm afraid I can't repay you...

378
00:27:17,211 --> 00:27:18,411
It's alright.

379
00:27:18,977 --> 00:27:21,877
Let's say, I'm here to have fun with you.

380
00:27:22,111 --> 00:27:25,211
Win or lose, it doesn't matter to me.

381
00:27:27,177 --> 00:27:30,044
No one is unfortunate their entire life.

382
00:27:42,077 --> 00:27:43,611
You're right about that.

383
00:27:44,877 --> 00:27:46,144
Then...

384
00:27:47,577 --> 00:27:48,644
I'll take it.

385
00:27:48,944 --> 00:27:49,944
Alright.

386
00:28:09,777 --> 00:28:11,911
I've been with my boss for years,

387
00:28:11,944 --> 00:28:15,244
but I have no idea she likes strawberry cake!

388
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:18,944
Actually, she doesn't like any sweets.

389
00:28:19,077 --> 00:28:20,244
Really?

390
00:28:21,477 --> 00:28:22,844
Your boss...

391
00:28:23,144 --> 00:28:26,111
seems easy to open up, but not actually.

392
00:28:26,311 --> 00:28:27,644
I see one door,

393
00:28:27,711 --> 00:28:30,711
then I see the second and third doors.

394
00:28:30,877 --> 00:28:32,677
Like I really know her, but I don't.

395
00:28:33,311 --> 00:28:34,477
So mysterious.

396
00:28:36,177 --> 00:28:38,177
She is not that mysterious.

397
00:28:38,344 --> 00:28:42,511
You see, she looks tough, but is so soft inside.

398
00:28:43,111 --> 00:28:47,044
Since she met you, she's even softer now!

399
00:28:47,711 --> 00:28:50,411
It surprised me to see that side of her.

400
00:28:50,477 --> 00:28:51,577
Are you serious?

401
00:28:53,744 --> 00:28:55,277
What do you think?

402
00:28:55,477 --> 00:28:56,977
Will it look good?

403
00:28:57,711 --> 00:28:59,777
The beauty of it doesn't matter,

404
00:28:59,911 --> 00:29:01,844
what matters is the dedication.

405
00:29:02,877 --> 00:29:05,711
- My boss will definitely love it. - I hope so.

406
00:29:06,811 --> 00:29:08,244
But I think...

407
00:29:08,277 --> 00:29:11,511
a cake isn't enough,

408
00:29:11,777 --> 00:29:15,644
you might need to impress her more with something more special.

409
00:29:15,777 --> 00:29:17,577
A special venue.

410
00:29:17,877 --> 00:29:21,211
A special item, or something that can't be found elsewhere.

411
00:29:25,177 --> 00:29:26,677
I think I've figured it out!

412
00:29:27,477 --> 00:29:32,177
It's gonna be a special night at the place where we first met!

413
00:29:35,144 --> 00:29:37,344
Thank you, Aiy.

414
00:29:37,577 --> 00:29:40,377
A romantic person like you should find someone!

415
00:29:41,544 --> 00:29:43,744
Help me find one then, Miss Lalin.

416
00:29:48,277 --> 00:29:50,044
Alright. Like this?

417
00:30:24,177 --> 00:30:25,577
What are you up to, dear?

418
00:30:27,944 --> 00:30:30,144
How...long have you been in here?

419
00:30:30,211 --> 00:30:32,077
Why didn't I hear your car engine or anything?

420
00:30:32,377 --> 00:30:33,611
I just arrived.

421
00:30:33,677 --> 00:30:36,611
I heard something in the kitchen, so I walked in.

422
00:30:37,444 --> 00:30:38,744
So...what were you doing?

423
00:30:40,877 --> 00:30:42,877
Umm, well...

424
00:30:43,777 --> 00:30:45,177
I'm hungry.

425
00:30:45,944 --> 00:30:47,711
I'm here to find something to eat.

426
00:30:48,211 --> 00:30:50,077
- Are you? - Umm, yes.

427
00:31:00,877 --> 00:31:02,111
What's on your cheek?

428
00:31:06,177 --> 00:31:07,177
What a mess.

429
00:31:09,877 --> 00:31:12,311
I wanna eat some pancakes,

430
00:31:12,777 --> 00:31:14,944
so I was practicing to make one.

431
00:31:17,644 --> 00:31:20,244
You can simply let the maids do it for you.

432
00:31:21,577 --> 00:31:23,777
Well, I don't want to bother them.

433
00:31:27,511 --> 00:31:29,011
You're acting weird, though.

434
00:31:29,277 --> 00:31:30,444
Why did you keep looking away?

435
00:31:30,844 --> 00:31:32,011
What's the matter?

436
00:31:33,477 --> 00:31:34,611
I didn't!

437
00:31:34,677 --> 00:31:36,377
No, I am staring at you now!

438
00:31:37,277 --> 00:31:38,277
You're the problem!

439
00:31:38,977 --> 00:31:40,644
You've been away the whole day,

440
00:31:40,777 --> 00:31:42,211
working and working.

441
00:31:42,444 --> 00:31:44,544
Where do I stand as your girlfriend?

442
00:31:45,077 --> 00:31:46,977
What are you mad about?

443
00:31:51,977 --> 00:31:53,577
I was just asking.

444
00:31:55,377 --> 00:31:57,877
- So what can I help you with? - No!

445
00:31:58,144 --> 00:31:59,577
Nothing!

446
00:31:59,611 --> 00:32:01,477
Hey, I've not hugged you or anything yet.

447
00:32:01,544 --> 00:32:03,811
- Just a hug. - Keep that for later. I'm hungry now!

448
00:32:04,111 --> 00:32:06,544
No hug, straight to the shower!

449
00:32:07,477 --> 00:32:09,344
Go! Go!!

450
00:32:11,211 --> 00:32:12,877
- You're good? - Sure!

451
00:32:42,944 --> 00:32:47,177
For the Cornerstone, the architect's approved in the first round.

452
00:32:49,877 --> 00:32:54,144
And the Singapore team just sent us the adjustment drafts yesterday.

453
00:32:55,211 --> 00:32:56,777
If there's nothing to change,

454
00:32:57,211 --> 00:33:00,644
we can proceed with the building permission by next month.

455
00:33:01,477 --> 00:33:03,077
Did Petra learn about this?

456
00:33:04,011 --> 00:33:05,011
Yes.

457
00:33:10,377 --> 00:33:11,377
Who's here?

458
00:33:12,011 --> 00:33:13,477
Is that Uncle Mek?

459
00:33:14,377 --> 00:33:15,711
He won't ring a bell.

460
00:33:16,844 --> 00:33:18,211
I'll check on that for you.

461
00:33:27,944 --> 00:33:28,977
Hello.

462
00:33:29,677 --> 00:33:31,777
We want to see Ms. Arisa Kulnavee.

463
00:33:33,177 --> 00:33:34,644
What is your matter, officers?

464
00:33:35,911 --> 00:33:37,444
We have a summons.

465
00:33:45,944 --> 00:33:49,011
I'm Arisa. What can I help you?

466
00:33:49,211 --> 00:33:52,511
Ms. Arisa, please present yourself at the police station.

467
00:34:04,277 --> 00:34:06,377
Ms. Arisa, do you know this person?

468
00:34:10,277 --> 00:34:12,177
Ms. Michelle, you are under arrest.

469
00:34:12,277 --> 00:34:13,144
Hold on...

470
00:34:14,177 --> 00:34:15,277
What the heck is this?

471
00:34:17,677 --> 00:34:18,777
I do know her.

472
00:34:19,311 --> 00:34:21,011
What is your relation with her?

473
00:34:22,577 --> 00:34:25,144
She used to be an investor for my company.

474
00:34:26,111 --> 00:34:28,644
After the financial investigation,

475
00:34:28,677 --> 00:34:31,644
we found many transactions made to your account,

476
00:34:31,977 --> 00:34:33,877
involving hundreds of millions.

477
00:34:34,177 --> 00:34:35,877
And what is that money for?

478
00:34:37,177 --> 00:34:39,677
The invested money is used as the company's cash flow,

479
00:34:40,944 --> 00:34:44,677
in hospitality and real estate businesses.

480
00:34:45,311 --> 00:34:48,077
Do you know that part of Ms. Michelle's money

481
00:34:48,277 --> 00:34:50,044
was from the scammer network?

482
00:35:00,711 --> 00:35:01,844
I have no clue, sir.

483
00:35:03,377 --> 00:35:08,311
Have you never wondered how she had that much money?

484
00:35:09,377 --> 00:35:10,877
Excuse me.

485
00:35:11,244 --> 00:35:12,244
My client

486
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:15,244
has run her entire business, legally.

487
00:35:15,777 --> 00:35:17,677
The investigation on money source

488
00:35:17,811 --> 00:35:21,144
is the responsibility of the relevant authorities, not my client.

489
00:35:21,277 --> 00:35:23,277
And the way you asked that question

490
00:35:23,877 --> 00:35:25,644
was too leading.

491
00:35:27,444 --> 00:35:30,211
We're now in the process of investigating all her financial trails.

492
00:35:30,544 --> 00:35:32,211
If your transactions

493
00:35:32,377 --> 00:35:35,211
are involved in money laundering or scammer networking,

494
00:35:35,411 --> 00:35:38,177
I'll summon you here for another statement.

495
00:35:39,244 --> 00:35:40,344
I'm fine with that.

496
00:35:47,044 --> 00:35:48,044
Ms. Arisa,

497
00:35:48,077 --> 00:35:51,311
you have known Ms. Michelle was involved with the scammer thing, right?

498
00:35:51,577 --> 00:35:54,877
The invested money's part of the money laundering, isn't it?

499
00:35:55,011 --> 00:35:57,111
Please give us a way.

500
00:35:57,211 --> 00:35:58,111
Wait a minute.

501
00:35:58,144 --> 00:36:01,344
Will your Cornerstone project with Petra proceed?

502
00:36:01,577 --> 00:36:05,277
Is your company involved in the money laundering scam?

503
00:36:05,444 --> 00:36:07,444
Everything is under the investigation.

504
00:36:08,011 --> 00:36:10,677
I will fully cooperate with the officers.

505
00:36:10,911 --> 00:36:12,677
So are you denying this?

506
00:36:12,744 --> 00:36:13,677
Yeah, is this true?

507
00:36:13,711 --> 00:36:15,811
- Please give us a way. - What are you gonna say?

508
00:36:15,844 --> 00:36:18,744
Please! Tell us!

509
00:36:32,677 --> 00:36:33,811
Dear...

510
00:36:34,844 --> 00:36:36,344
I've seen the news.

511
00:36:36,944 --> 00:36:38,344
What happened?

512
00:36:41,411 --> 00:36:43,344
No need to care about it that much.

513
00:36:44,177 --> 00:36:46,377
I have no clue where they learned about this.

514
00:36:47,544 --> 00:36:49,577
They all got the same brief.

515
00:36:50,111 --> 00:36:52,611
Just tell me what happened.

516
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:55,277
You know what, people are gossiping

517
00:36:55,511 --> 00:36:59,577
that you have this much money because of the scamming business.

518
00:37:07,844 --> 00:37:09,677
I know Michelle, that's true.

519
00:37:11,711 --> 00:37:14,811
But I have no clue she was running an illegal business.

520
00:37:18,044 --> 00:37:20,811
She helped me build this company.

521
00:37:25,244 --> 00:37:26,877
But I never knew...

522
00:37:27,544 --> 00:37:28,844
that all the money

523
00:37:30,144 --> 00:37:32,244
was from a scam scheme.

524
00:37:36,177 --> 00:37:37,711
That's okay.

525
00:37:38,944 --> 00:37:40,777
You didn't know that, you're good.

526
00:37:42,477 --> 00:37:44,344
If you're not involved,

527
00:37:44,411 --> 00:37:46,544
no one can place the blame on you.

528
00:38:04,744 --> 00:38:06,311
Thanks, Lalin.

529
00:38:08,644 --> 00:38:11,144
You got many past stories, though.

530
00:38:11,677 --> 00:38:13,044
Anything else I need to know?

531
00:38:17,411 --> 00:38:18,611
Many more.

532
00:38:19,911 --> 00:38:21,244
Are you sure you can handle me?

533
00:38:25,477 --> 00:38:29,544
Love is about embracing one another's mistakes in the past.

534
00:38:30,411 --> 00:38:32,711
Everyone has a second chance, always.

535
00:38:33,777 --> 00:38:36,677
Oh, are you a life coach by any chance?

536
00:38:37,311 --> 00:38:38,344
I'm doing great, right?

537
00:38:38,544 --> 00:38:39,777
You cheered me up so well.

538
00:38:45,977 --> 00:38:46,977
Wait a sec.

539
00:38:49,344 --> 00:38:50,644
Hello.

540
00:38:50,877 --> 00:38:53,577
Oops! Sorry, I'm gonna be there right now.

541
00:38:56,477 --> 00:38:58,211
I have a meeting to attend.

542
00:38:58,777 --> 00:38:59,677
Are you leaving now?

543
00:38:59,744 --> 00:39:02,544
Yeah, I've been called in. See you later!

544
00:39:59,295 --> 00:40:00,455
What big news.

545
00:40:02,055 --> 00:40:03,175
How did you explain yourself?

546
00:40:04,895 --> 00:40:06,335
Why did I have to do that?

547
00:40:07,295 --> 00:40:08,615
The truth remains.

548
00:40:10,215 --> 00:40:12,575
Besides, I haven't done anything wrong.

549
00:40:13,815 --> 00:40:15,575
I've already told the officers everything.

550
00:40:16,935 --> 00:40:18,255
But it already happened.

551
00:40:19,655 --> 00:40:22,495
Being involved with someone who has done an illegal business

552
00:40:23,415 --> 00:40:24,815
is not a minor issue.

553
00:40:25,055 --> 00:40:27,095
Not only you will be affected,

554
00:40:27,575 --> 00:40:29,455
but also the companies you hold shares in

555
00:40:29,695 --> 00:40:30,895
will be investigated, too.

556
00:40:31,855 --> 00:40:33,095
More importantly,

557
00:40:33,735 --> 00:40:34,735
what about Lalin?

558
00:40:36,215 --> 00:40:37,695
Her reputation might also be ruined by this.

559
00:40:41,815 --> 00:40:43,335
Don't worry too much about that,

560
00:40:44,735 --> 00:40:46,895
I won't let this damage her reputation.

561
00:40:48,175 --> 00:40:49,575
I hope that's true.

562
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:52,775
Soon,

563
00:40:52,975 --> 00:40:54,775
Lalin will finally see

564
00:40:55,415 --> 00:40:57,055
who the real

565
00:40:57,775 --> 00:40:58,775
Arisa is.

566
00:41:28,575 --> 00:41:29,975
It's true, though.

567
00:41:30,455 --> 00:41:32,375
When it comes to a scammer thing,

568
00:41:32,855 --> 00:41:35,375
people are ready to judge you.

569
00:41:35,975 --> 00:41:38,255
It takes ages for the result to come,

570
00:41:38,855 --> 00:41:40,735
and by that time, the news will have spread widely.

571
00:41:42,335 --> 00:41:45,855
The truth comes too late, no one waits to hear it.

572
00:41:47,295 --> 00:41:48,295
I see.

573
00:41:49,215 --> 00:41:52,135
We tend to believe what we want to believe.

574
00:41:52,575 --> 00:41:53,575
You're right.

575
00:41:54,815 --> 00:41:58,495
But at least, you still got Lalin by your side.

576
00:42:00,615 --> 00:42:02,455
When life's ruined,

577
00:42:03,215 --> 00:42:06,335
having someone by your side is so important.

578
00:42:07,735 --> 00:42:11,295
Lalin is just as great as her dad, Thana.

579
00:42:15,815 --> 00:42:17,295
When I was a teenager,

580
00:42:17,375 --> 00:42:19,175
I went to study in the States.

581
00:42:19,695 --> 00:42:21,535
And I fell in love with a foreign guy.

582
00:42:22,815 --> 00:42:25,535
My family really looked down on him.

583
00:42:26,095 --> 00:42:28,215
Eventually, we couldn't make it.

584
00:42:29,295 --> 00:42:31,335
I was told to fly back to Thailand.

585
00:42:32,135 --> 00:42:35,335
My parents did everything so that I couldn't communicate with him.

586
00:42:36,975 --> 00:42:38,495
But there was only Thana,

587
00:42:40,055 --> 00:42:42,255
who said goodbye on my behalf.

588
00:42:43,455 --> 00:42:45,415
He consoled me and everything.

589
00:42:47,335 --> 00:42:51,055
I felt so lucky to have him as a young brother.

590
00:42:54,415 --> 00:42:56,295
But on the day he passed away for good,

591
00:42:57,815 --> 00:42:59,295
I learned that...

592
00:43:00,615 --> 00:43:03,535
life isn't always that kind to us.

593
00:43:05,695 --> 00:43:07,095
From that day onwards,

594
00:43:08,095 --> 00:43:10,135
I had no one else on my side,

595
00:43:10,535 --> 00:43:13,535
no family or friends,

596
00:43:14,735 --> 00:43:16,615
only me.

597
00:43:20,495 --> 00:43:23,375
Have you talked to Weiling?

598
00:43:24,295 --> 00:43:26,935
She's still your sister-in-law, isn't she?

599
00:43:29,135 --> 00:43:32,895
You still can't tell I hate that bitch?

600
00:43:34,215 --> 00:43:37,495
The whole time she was dating my brother,

601
00:43:38,375 --> 00:43:40,735
I knew she was secretly dating someone else.

602
00:43:46,495 --> 00:43:48,215
Acting like a perfect queen.

603
00:43:48,575 --> 00:43:50,615
Scolding me, saying I was a compulsive gambler.

604
00:43:52,095 --> 00:43:54,375
She was no better than me.

605
00:43:57,935 --> 00:44:00,255
Did Mr. Thana know about this?

606
00:44:02,735 --> 00:44:04,575
Just like you said,

607
00:44:05,135 --> 00:44:08,535
we all wanted to believe in what we felt like.

608
00:44:16,295 --> 00:44:18,335
Don't tell Lalin about this.

609
00:44:19,695 --> 00:44:23,455
Let this die with someone old like me.

610
00:44:31,735 --> 00:44:33,015
OK.

611
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:44,055
Hey...

612
00:44:44,735 --> 00:44:46,295
Is the shop closed?

613
00:44:46,575 --> 00:44:48,775
No, you can come!

614
00:45:09,375 --> 00:45:13,175
♫Happy birthday to you♫

615
00:45:13,615 --> 00:45:17,935
♫Happy birthday to you!♫

616
00:45:18,215 --> 00:45:22,735
♫Happy birthday, happy birthday♫

617
00:45:24,135 --> 00:45:28,815
♫Happy birthday to you♫

618
00:45:30,575 --> 00:45:32,095
Make a wish.

619
00:45:41,975 --> 00:45:43,775
What did you wish?

620
00:45:45,295 --> 00:45:47,135
I wished...

621
00:45:47,215 --> 00:45:48,615
us...

622
00:45:49,295 --> 00:45:50,335
Better not say it.

623
00:45:51,095 --> 00:45:52,895
I'm afraid it won't come true.

624
00:45:57,015 --> 00:45:58,895
I don't think I need to guess

625
00:45:59,135 --> 00:46:01,015
how you found out when my birthday was.

626
00:46:01,615 --> 00:46:03,935
Only Aiy knew about this.

627
00:46:05,295 --> 00:46:07,335
Don't blame her,

628
00:46:08,255 --> 00:46:10,295
I just wanted to surprise you.

629
00:46:11,695 --> 00:46:13,495
I told you,

630
00:46:14,095 --> 00:46:15,695
I'm not into birthdays.

631
00:46:16,615 --> 00:46:18,375
And I don't like surprises either.

632
00:46:21,495 --> 00:46:25,215
I don't know what you've been through in the past.

633
00:46:26,335 --> 00:46:28,335
But it's time...

634
00:46:28,615 --> 00:46:31,855
to recreate good memories.

635
00:46:32,495 --> 00:46:35,135
I hope you can leave bad things behind.

636
00:46:35,455 --> 00:46:37,975
If you can't leave some,

637
00:46:38,375 --> 00:46:40,215
share them with me.

638
00:46:41,935 --> 00:46:45,295
I want to laugh and cry with you.

639
00:46:52,935 --> 00:46:55,295
But the surprise isn't just that.

640
00:46:55,775 --> 00:46:56,815
You got more?

641
00:46:57,295 --> 00:46:59,175
Umm! Follow me.

642
00:48:01,055 --> 00:48:04,015
Can I be your new memory?

643
00:48:05,335 --> 00:48:08,575
A memory that will make you smile forever.

644
00:48:14,455 --> 00:48:15,615
Thanks.

645
00:50:14,055 --> 00:50:18,615
Next week, my mom is holding a violence-against-women charity.

646
00:50:19,215 --> 00:50:20,375
Sometimes,

647
00:50:20,695 --> 00:50:24,775
it's the time we have to open our relationship to public.

648
00:50:25,175 --> 00:50:26,655
For Arisa,

649
00:50:26,735 --> 00:50:29,095
I already got something to attack her.

650
00:50:29,615 --> 00:50:30,415
What is it?

651
00:50:31,095 --> 00:50:32,575
Hey, Kee!

652
00:50:34,495 --> 00:50:35,575
Who is that, dear?

653
00:50:35,855 --> 00:50:37,295
Why do you seem close to her?

654
00:50:37,575 --> 00:50:38,295
An old friend of mine.

655
00:50:38,615 --> 00:50:40,495
How did you know that woman?

656
00:50:40,655 --> 00:50:41,935
Tell me about it.

657
00:50:42,175 --> 00:50:43,375
I'll pay you for that.

658
00:50:43,655 --> 00:50:46,455
So Lalin will know what Arisa hides from her.

659
00:50:46,815 --> 00:50:49,535
No matter how severe your past is,

660
00:50:50,615 --> 00:50:54,375
I want you to know you will always have me by your side.
